Cargo.lock — auto-generated dependency lockfile for the ctx-* workspace (cargo-generated, `version = 4` format). Never hand-edit; regenerate via `cargo build`/`cargo update`, which rewrites it wholesale.

Pins exact versions/checksums for the workspace crates `ctx-brief`, `ctx-cage`, `ctx-context`, `ctx-core`, `ctx-scan`, `ctx-summarize`, `ctx-verify`, and all transitive third-party deps. Notable third-party choices: `clap` (v4, derive) for CLI parsing across most binaries, `thiserror` for error types, `ignore`/`globset`/`walkdir` for filesystem traversal (used by ctx-scan and ctx-summarize), `sha2` for hashing (ctx-core), `nix`/`rustix` for low-level OS calls (ctx-cage sandboxing), and `serde`/`serde_json` for serialization.

Editing implications: adding a dependency to any workspace crate's Cargo.toml requires running `cargo build` (or `cargo update`) to refresh this file — manual additions will be overwritten and can desync from actual resolved versions. The crate `zmij` (pulled in via `serde_json`) is a non-obvious transitive dependency, not a typo. No behavior lives here; it's purely a resolution snapshot.